00:41.648 --> 00:43.749
The road is long.

00:43.751 --> 00:46.285
The path uncertain.

00:46.287 --> 00:50.389
For so many of us, the
journey is one of solitude.

00:50.391 --> 00:55.694
We tell ourselves we must
walk this arduous road alone.

00:55.696 --> 00:58.931
Face whatever comes,
no matter how terrible.

00:58.933 --> 01:01.700
Some of us call on angels

01:01.702 --> 01:05.904
to spread their wings and protect us.

01:05.906 --> 01:08.407
Others long to see the path,

01:08.409 --> 01:10.776
hoping they will come to know the way

01:10.778 --> 01:12.845
through the Lord's nourishment.

01:12.847 --> 01:15.814
What if we are shown the way?

01:15.816 --> 01:18.017
Will we continue on this road,

01:18.019 --> 01:21.820
alone, blind, and afraid?

01:21.822 --> 01:26.925
Or will we have the
strength to follow his path?

01:26.927 --> 01:31.030
That is why I am here
today... To honor a man

01:31.032 --> 01:33.832
who sees with better
eyes than the rest of us.

01:33.834 --> 01:38.904
He has shown us God's path to salvation.

01:38.906 --> 01:42.708
Through his ministry, he
has saved so many lives,

01:42.710 --> 01:43.876
including mine.

01:43.878 --> 01:46.979
My husband, Jacob Fuller.

02:04.664 --> 02:06.799
That better not be Kyle.

02:06.801 --> 02:08.834
Shut your trap.

02:08.836 --> 02:10.803
We're gonna stop the first place we see.

02:10.805 --> 02:11.937
We're gonna do what?

02:11.939 --> 02:13.739
Daddy is drunk.

02:13.741 --> 02:15.908
He needs to sleep it off in
an honest-to-goodness bed.

02:15.910 --> 02:17.042
Let him sleep right there.

02:17.044 --> 02:18.410
You should keep driving to Mexico.

02:18.412 --> 02:20.479
I'm not going to Mexico.

02:20.481 --> 02:22.715
If anything, I'd drive back to Bethel,

02:22.717 --> 02:24.416
but I can't do that, either.

02:24.418 --> 02:25.884
Since when do you call all the shots?

02:25.886 --> 02:27.686
Since now.

02:27.688 --> 02:28.954
There... The closest place

02:28.956 --> 02:30.823
is something called the Dew Drop Inn.

02:30.825 --> 02:32.358
Sounds cute.

02:38.898 --> 02:40.899
Housekeeping!

02:43.036 --> 02:44.403
Time to clean your room, son.

02:44.405 --> 02:45.871
Uh, we... We don't need it.

02:46.973 --> 02:49.108
You better not be making a mess in there.

02:49.110 --> 02:50.976
You see, the thing is, ma'am, my, um...

02:50.978 --> 02:52.444
My girlfriend is still asleep.

02:52.446 --> 02:53.812
You know, we kind of had a...

02:53.814 --> 02:55.914
You know, late night last night.

02:55.916 --> 02:57.983
You can come back tomorrow,
though, if you like.

02:57.985 --> 02:59.518
I'll come back when I damn well please.

02:59.520 --> 03:03.322
Okay. Thank you.

03:03.324 --> 03:04.923
- I wish you would let me tell you...
- Shut up. No talking.

03:04.925 --> 03:06.692
We need to think. Okay?

03:06.694 --> 03:08.627
Half the ticket takers on the Rio Grande

03:08.629 --> 03:10.362
are gonna have copies of our mug shot.

03:10.364 --> 03:12.331
We need a way across. We need it right now.

03:12.333 --> 03:13.799
Just listen to me.

03:13.801 --> 03:15.434
I should have listened
to Uncle Eddie. You know?

03:15.436 --> 03:17.069
Guys like us, we're always
talking about getting out,

03:17.071 --> 03:18.771
living in paradise.

03:18.773 --> 03:20.439
You know, talk about it all day long.

03:20.441 --> 03:22.074
We never actually get there.

03:22.076 --> 03:23.075
Seth.

03:23.077 --> 03:24.376
Something happened to me.

03:24.378 --> 03:25.944
Yes, Richard.

03:25.946 --> 03:27.446
Something is happening.

03:27.448 --> 03:29.381
Now, I have tried to understand it.

03:29.383 --> 03:31.850
I have. But I can't.

03:31.852 --> 03:33.419
And somehow, I don't think

03:33.421 --> 03:35.854
that you're gonna be able
to explain that to me.

03:38.858 --> 03:41.060
I could see inside her.

03:41.062 --> 03:42.761
What the hell does that even mean?

03:42.763 --> 03:44.063
I could see.

03:44.065 --> 03:45.764
I knew she was gonna hurt me.

03:46.901 --> 03:48.367
I knew it. It was in her eyes.

03:48.369 --> 03:49.868
And I don't know how
to explain it right now,

03:49.870 --> 03:51.103
but I want to figure it out.

03:51.105 --> 03:52.671
Well, you're not gonna figure it out here.

03:52.673 --> 03:54.473
All right? We cannot stay here.

03:56.876 --> 03:59.411
You want to know what
else Uncle Eddie says?

03:59.413 --> 04:01.680
What?

04:01.682 --> 04:03.415
It's how we're gonna get across, too.

04:03.417 --> 04:04.983
What, Richard? What is it?

04:04.985 --> 04:07.886
There's an old Indian
saying he told me once.

04:09.889 --> 04:12.358
"Eyes find eyes."

04:12.360 --> 04:15.861
You see, our eyes are
the source of our energy.

04:15.863 --> 04:17.696
You can always feel somebody's eyes on you,

04:17.697 --> 04:18.964
but what you're actually feeling

04:18.966 --> 04:22.101
is their energy directed right at you.

04:22.103 --> 04:23.902
Now, what happens if you close your eyes?

04:23.904 --> 04:24.903
What?

04:24.905 --> 04:27.806
You cut off your energy.

04:27.808 --> 04:29.074
If you can just shut down,

04:29.076 --> 04:31.043
not only will people not see you,

04:31.045 --> 04:32.878
but they'll see through you.

04:32.880 --> 04:35.481
The greatest cat burglar in
the history of cat burglars

04:35.483 --> 04:36.715
taught him that.

04:36.717 --> 04:38.450
Close our eyes.

04:38.452 --> 04:40.853
That's your plan? Close our eyes?

04:42.021 --> 04:44.156
Okay. I got to get out of here.

04:44.158 --> 04:46.892
All right, you, uh, brush up
on your Spanish or something.

04:55.135 --> 04:56.969
I got dibs on the bed.

04:56.971 --> 04:58.937
I'm not sleeping with dad.

04:58.939 --> 05:00.806
I'm too old for that.

05:08.948 --> 05:11.150
What in the world?

05:11.152 --> 05:12.551
It's just some weirdo.

05:17.857 --> 05:20.526
What is his problem?

